Prime Minister and wife Samantha joined worshippers at the Gravesend Gurdwara in Kent . 
  The couple joined a parade carrying the Sikh holy book to the temple . 
  Mr Cameron gave a speech at the festival of Vaisakhi in a traditional orange patka . 
  He said he 'believed in aspiration' and that the 'only limit to one's potential is their own talent' It was the Prime Minister and his wife's first visit to Kent during the general election campaign . 
  Comes just a day after the couple attended the Festival of Life in London . 
 